{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778899411416,"sessionID":"ses_1d1556aa2ffeUcnC8oDnD6tUmW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-98a4dd2afdc2901d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"Please provide as much information as you can: \\n\\n* **Suggested term label:**\\n\\nvesicle membrane tethering activity\\n\\n* **Definition (free text)**\\n\\nMF vesicle membrane tethering activity\\nA membrane-membrane adaptor activity that provides the first point of contact and physically bridges between the vesicle membrane and its target before they are in close apposition prior to vesicle docking and fusion.\\n\\n\\n* **Reference, in format PMID:#######**\\n\\nPMID:19887069\\n\\n* **Gene product name and ID to be annotated to this term**\\n\\npombe\\nuso1\\ngrp1\\nrud3\\nsec3\\nexo70\\nsec15\\ndrp1/sec39\\n\\n\\n* **Parent term(s)**\\n\\nGO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity\\nextend def to include \\\"vesicle\\\" \\n\\nThe binding activity of a molecule that brings together two membranes, either via membrane lipid binding or by interacting with a membrane protein, to establish or maintain the localization of the protein, protein complex or organelle.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n* **Any other information**\\n\",\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws78saEF\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n10:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please create a new term vesicle membrane tethering activity. In addition to PMID:19887069 that focuses on ER-Golgi membrane traffic, include a review article that covers synaptic vesicle transport and targeting.\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-13T20:43:11Z\",\n12:       \"